<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: External_model_arm  Entity: External_geometric_model  
   <express_ref linkend="external_model:arm:External_model_arm.External_geometric_model"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="External_model_arm.External_geometric_model">
An <b>External_geometric_model</b> is a type of 3D <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model"/>

 whose content is provided in an external file.
<p>The set of items of the <b>External_geometric_model</b> contains only one element that shall be an <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement"/>.
This <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement"/>

 specifies the reference location and orientation with respect to which placement of the <b>External_geometric_model</b> in other <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model"/>s shall be defined.
</p>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: External_model_arm  Entity: External_geometric_model  Attribute: SELF\Representation.items 
   <express_ref linkend="external_model:arm:External_model_arm.External_geometric_model..items"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description
  linkend="External_model_arm.External_geometric_model.items">
  <p>
    the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement"/>
  that defines the reference position or orientation of the
  <b>External_geometric_model</b>.
</p>
<note>
Most of times, the position is the origin point of the coordinate space and the orientation matrix is the identity matrix.
</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: External_model_arm  Entity: External_geometric_model  Attribute: external_file 
   <express_ref linkend="external_model:arm:External_model_arm.External_geometric_model.external_file"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="External_model_arm.External_geometric_model.external_file">
the <express_ref linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.Digital_file"/>

 that contains the external geometry information.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: External_model_arm  Entity: External_geometric_model  Where: WR1 
   ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="External_model_arm.External_geometric_model.wr:WR1">
the <b>External_geometric_model</b> shall be a 3D model.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: External_model_arm  Entity: External_geometric_model  Where: WR2 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description
  linkend="External_model_arm.External_geometric_model.wr:WR2">
  <p>
    The <express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation_context"/>
  of the <b>External_geometric_model</b> shall be of kind 'external'.
</p>
<note>
  Because the <b>External_geometric_model</b> entity is a subtype of <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model"/>, the <express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation_context"/>

<express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation_context"/>

 of the <b>External_geometric_model</b> is actually a <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_coordinate_space"/>.
</note>
</ext_description>

</ext_descriptions>
